Node.js allows us to run JavaScript on the server. Express is the most popular framework for building web servers.

## 1. Basic Server
```javascript
const express = require('express');
const app = express();

app.get('/', (req, res) => {
  res.send('Hello GenSpark!');
});

app.listen(3000);
```

## 2. Middlewares
Functions that have access to the request and response objects. Used for logging, authentication, and parsing data.

